HEADWORD: Pipette
<hw>Pi*pette"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., dim. of
<ets>pipe</ets>.]</ety> <def>A small glass tube, often with an
enlargement or bulb in the middle, and usually graduated, -- used for
transferring or delivering measured quantities.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

